%I A158529 #27 Jun 13 2026 11:36:49
%S A158529 29,569,1289,41609,147449,2322569,2842589,7096889,7485689,10074269,
%T A158529 16208669,21288989,33802589,54819209,56610569,57699209,59814749,
%U A158529 115218749,118069949,126427529,134235389,149670749,196448249,240746249
%N A158529 List of primes p with following properties: p = prime(m-1) for some m, p+7 is a square and is equal to prime(m+1)-1.
%C A158529 Conjecture: If the condition holds, prime(m-1) and prime(m) are twin primes of the form 10k+9 and 10k+11, i.e. the last digits of the twin prime pairs are 9 and 1. The 9 ending is obvious in this sequence. The table of the first 101 terms was computed using Zak Seidov's table.
%C A158529 Proof of conjecture: Suppose p = prime(m-1) is a term with p + 7 = x^2.  Now prime(m) must be p + 2 (it can't be p + 4 because one of p, p+4 and p+8 would be divisible by 3, and it can't be p + 6 = x^2-1 = (x-1)*(x+1)). As an even square, p + 7 ends in 0, 4 or 6, but it can't be 0 because p + 2 would be divisible by 5 and can't be 4 because p + 8 would be divisible by 5. The only possibility is that p + 7 ends in 6, i.e. p ends in 9. - _Robert Israel_, Jun 12 2026
%H A158529 Robert Israel, <a href="/A158529/b158529.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a> (first 101 terms from Cino Hilliard)
%H A158529 Sebastian Martin Ruiz, <a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/primenumbers/message/19899">Integer then equal</a> [Broken link]
%H A158529 Sebastian Martin Ruiz and others, <a href="/A158460/a158460.txt">Integers then Equals</a>, digest of 7 messages in primenumbers Yahoo group, Mar 14 - Mar 20, 2009.
%e A158529 For m = 11, prime(11-1)=29, 29+7=36; prime(11+1)=37, 37-1=36. So 29 is the first entry in the sequence.
%p A158529 R:= NULL: count:= 0:
%p A158529 for y from 0 by 10 while count < 100 do
%p A158529 for x in [y+4,y+6] do
%p A158529   p:= x^2-7;
%p A158529   if isprime(p) and isprime(p+2) and isprime(p+8)  then
%p A158529     R:= R,p; count:= count+1;
%p A158529 fi od od:
%p A158529 R; # _Robert Israel_, Jun 12 2026
%t A158529 ppQ[{a_,b_}]:=Module[{s=Prime[a+1]-1},IntegerQ[Sqrt[s]]&&b+7==s]; Select[ Table[ {n,Prime[n-1]},{n,2,133*10^5}],ppQ][[All,2]] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Jul 31 2020 *)
%o A158529 (PARI) isok(p) = if (isprime(p), my(x); issquare(x=p+7) && (x==nextprime(nextprime(p+1)+1)-1)); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 12 2026
%K A158529 nonn,changed
